.SH NAME
.PP
greenhouse - A Python-based management interface for greenhouse
automation.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]python3 main.py\f[R] [OPTIONS]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\f[B]GreenhousePython\f[R] is a graphical and command-line utility
designed to control greenhouse hardware.
It provides interfaces for camera monitoring, irrigation (water control)
for multiple garden beds, and light intensity scaling.
.PP
The application uses the GTK4 toolkit for its graphical interface and
Typer for command-line interactions.
.SH CONFIGURATION
.PP
The application requires a configuration file named \f[B]cfg.txt\f[R]
located in the working directory.
.SS Required fields in cfg.txt:
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]beds\f[R]: The number of garden beds to initialize for water
control.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]file_name_prefix\f[R]: The prefix used for saving and retrieving
camera images.
.SH INTERFACE SECTIONS
.PP
The interface is divided into the following notebook pages:
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]Camera Control\f[R]: Displays placeholders or active streams from
the greenhouse camera.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]Water Control\f[R]: Provides individual control tabs for each
\[lq]Bed\[rq] defined in the configuration.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]Light Control\f[R]: Features a slider to adjust light intensity
from 0 to 1.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]Misc\f[R]: Additional system controls and settings.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]0\f[R]: Success.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]1\f[R]: Failure (e.g., missing cfg.txt or dependency errors).
